Lab 03: Operating System Detection with Nmap (-O)
Objective

The purpose of this lab is to identify the operating system running on the target host using Nmap's OS fingerprinting capabilities. Accurate OS identification helps security professionals understand the target environment, prioritize relevant vulnerabilities, and plan defensive or assessment activities.

Scan Command
db_nmap -Pn -n -O 172.16.59.129
Command Breakdown
Option	Description
db_nmap	Runs Nmap through the Metasploit Framework and stores results in its database.
-Pn	Skips host discovery and assumes the target is online.
-n	Disables DNS resolution to speed up the scan.
-O	Enables operating system detection through TCP/IP fingerprinting.
Executive Summary

The scan successfully identified the target as a Linux-based system and estimated that it is running a Linux 2.6.x kernel. The host is one network hop away and appears to be running inside a VMware virtual environment.

Unlike service-version scans, the -O option focuses on identifying the host operating system rather than the versions of applications listening on open ports.

