Conclusion

The scan successfully identified the target as a Linux 2.6.x system running in a VMware virtual environment with a significant number of exposed services. While this configuration is expected for the intentionally vulnerable Metasploitable 2 training platform, the same findings on a production host would warrant a detailed review of operating system support status, exposed services, and overall hardening measures. This lab illustrates how OS detection complements service enumeration by providing context that helps guide subsequent security assessment activities.
